race.comment: SHOCKLETZ (11) looks the horse to beat. She was a progressive staying 3yo over the Winter and resumed with plenty of dash at Sandown Hillside over a mile, sprinting quickly with 58kg to score well. She drops sharply in weight and more ground will only suit her better. Tipping she can go right on with it. AL DUCA (9) continues to race very well, run down by a progressive one at Caulfield last time out when carrying the big weight which he now drops right down in. Lane sticks with him from the good gate and he'll take some beating. FORTUNE (5) has won two of his past three and has to be respected. ZIRYAB (6) is through two fast races and could be an improver.
